#Text=County Kilkenny
#Text=County Kilkenny ( Irish : Contae Chill Chainnigh ) is in Southeast Ireland , in the province of Leinster .
#Text=It is a land-locked county , surrounded by the counties of Carlow , Laois , Wexford , Waterford and Tipperary .
#Text=It has a population of 95,000 .
#Text=Cities

#Text=( Cill Chainnigh , " church of Cainnech " ) – the county 's capital city has an attractive " Medieval Mile " of historic buildings between Kilkenny Castle and St Canice 's Cathedral & Round Tower
#Text=Towns
#Text=- small town really off the tourist trail .
#Text=It has a nice square and a fine Roman Catholic church just behind the square .
#Text=-
#Text=check out The Moat , a great example of a Motte-and-bailey , and visit the childhood home of Edmund Rice , the founder of the Irish Christian Brothers .
#Text=- The main town in north Kilkenny .
#Text=Coal was mined here for over 300 years .
#Text=Visit Castlecomer
#Text=Discover Park and Footprints in Coal Experience to learn more .
#Text=- A beautiful town near Waterford City , made famous by the song " The Rose of Mooncoin " .
#Text=-
#Text=On the river Nore , this town is famous for Jerpoint Abbey , Kilfane Glen gardens , and Mount Juliet Golf Course .
#Text=Villages
#Text=- Home of Duiske Abbey , Graiguenamanagh is a popular place for walking and hillclimbing .
#Text=The town itself is very pretty .
#Text=- a beautiful little village on the river Nore .
#Text=It was the setting for the film " Circle of Friends " .

column1: #Text=It has a lovely square .
#Text=It also has an impressive multi span stone bridge .
#Text=Just above the village , are Woodstock Gardens , which are being restored to period 1840 - 1890 .
#Text=- the only place in Ireland to see battle in the Wars of the Roses .
#Text=A pretty village famous for its " Tower " also known as Sham Castle .
#Text=Tourist Information
#Text=Kilkenny Tourist Office is located on Rose Inn St , in Kilkenny City .
#Text=It has lots of information about the city and county .
#Text=Climate
#Text=Kilkenny is in the centre of The Sunny South East .
#Text=It has the most extreme climate in Ireland mainly because it is not affected by the sea , but do n't get too worried .
#Text=The highest recorded temperature ever was 33.3°C .
#Text=There is on average , 4 days of snow a year .
#Text=By train
#Text=All the stations in County Kilkenny are on the Dublin – Waterford line , which serves Dublin , Athy , Carlow , Bagenalstown , Kilkenny .
#Text=Thomastown and Waterford .
#Text=There are 6 trains a day in each direction .
#Text=The railway stations in or near County Kilkenny are :
#Text=Kilkenny Railway Station ( MacDonagh Station ) , ☏ +35356 772-2024 .
#Text=Thomastown Railway Station , Station Road , Thomastown , ☏ +35356 772-4218 .
#Text=Waterford Railway Station ( Plunkett Station ) , ☏ +35351873401 .
#Text=Muine Bheag Train Station ( Bagenalstown Train Station ) .
#Text=This station is not in County Kilkenny , but just over the border , 4km away , in County Carlow .
#Text=Tickets and timetable information can be got at the stations , online or by phone ( 01 7034070 between 09.00-17.00 Monday - Friday ) .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Roads
#Text=Train
#Text=See
#Text=Jenkinstown Park ( 10 km north of Kilkenny , 11 km south of Castlecomer , off N78 .
#Text=) .
#Text=The forested park is a nice place for a walk or a picnic .
#Text=There are deer and some rare trees .
#Text=During April the forest is carpeted by bluebells .
#Text=It was once part of the Bryan-Bellew Estate , of which castle ruins and walls can still be seen .
#Text=Thomas Moore wrote The Last Rose of Summer while staying at Jenkinstown House .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Heritage Ireland Sites
#Text=There are four Heritage Ireland Sites in County Kilkenny .
#Text=These sites are maintained by the Office of Public Works ( OPW ) and the Department of the Environment , Heritage and Local Government .
#Text=A heritage card , which is valid for a year costs :
#Text=adult € 21 , senior citizen € 16 , student € 8 , family € 55 .
#Text=Jerpoint Abbey , Thomastown .
#Text=Built in the 12th Century .
#Text=It is Ireland 's finest Cistercian monastic ruin with a magnificently sculptured cloister arcade .
#Text=Kilkenny Castle , Kilkenny .
#Text=This stunning Norman Castle , which is the dominant feature in the city , is its principal attraction .
#Text=Its huge forested gardens are beautiful to walk during the day .
#Text=Dunmore Caves , Dunmore ( 10km from Kilkenny city , off the N78 ) , ☏ +35356 776-7726 , fax : +35356 776-7262 , ✉ dunmorecaves@opw.ie .
#Text=9:30 - 17:00 ( 15:00 Nov-Feb , 18:00 Mid Jun-Mid Sept ) .
#Text=The show cave is incredibly well developed and a wonder to walk around .
#Text=St. Mary 's Church , Gowran , ☏ +35356 772-6894 , ✉ info@heritageireland.ie .
#Text=28th May - 16th Sept : Daily 09:30-18:00. A 13th century church .
#Text=Do
#Text=Brandon Hill , Graiguenamanagh .
#Text=The highest mountain in County Kilkenny is an easy climb of 515m ( 1,6790ft ) .
#Text=At the top there great views of the surrounding counties .
#Text=There is a cairn , an old cross and a plaque pointing out the features in the surrounding landscape .
#Text=Walk the South Leinster Way .
#Text=This is a walk that covers 102km(64miles ) from Kildavin , Co Carlow to Carrick-on-Suir , Co Tipperary .
#Text=It passes through medieval towns and ancient sites , river valleys , forests and by the slopes of Mount Leinster .
#Text=Golf is very popular in Kilkenny .
#Text=Callan Golf Club , Geraldine , Callan , ☏ +35356 772-5136 , ✉ info@callangolfclub.com .
#Text=An 18-hole course established in 1929 .
#Text=Castlecomer Golf Club , Dromgoole , Castlecomer , ☏ +35356 444-1139 .
#Text=Kilkenny Golf Course , Glendine , ☏ +35356 776-5400 , fax : +35356 772-3593 , ✉ enquiries@kilkennygolfclub.com .
#Text=A members owned 18-hole golf course .
#Text=Can rent clubs .
#Text=Green fees € 25 - 45.
#Text=Mount Juliet Golf Course ( 20 minutes from Kilkenny ) .
#Text=This golf course was designed by Jack Nicklaus and is one of the top golf courses in the country .
#Text=It often holds international golf tournments .
#Text=Green fees € 70 - 150.
#Text=Mountain View Golf Club , Kiltorcan , Ballyhale ( South of Ballyhale on the main Dublin-Waterford Road ( N9 ) ) , ☏ +35356 776-8122 , ✉ info@mviewgolf.com .
#Text=Drink
#Text=Kilkenny is famous for two beers - the Kilkenny beer and the Smithwicks ale , famous the world over as the distinct taste .
#Text=Why not try them on your visit to the County ?
#Text=Newspapers
#Text=Kilkenny People .
#Text=Weekly paper , out Wednesday .
#Text=This is the largest selling newspaper in the South East .
#Text=Covers Kilkenny city and county , with news , sports , property and entertainment listings .
#Text=James Joyce referred to this paper in Ulysses .
